Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Golden Gate Bridge
Description: possibly the most beautiful, certainly the most photographed, bridge in the world.

Name: Seattle Great Wheel
Description: It's the tallest Ferris wheel on the west coast of the United States.

Name: Santa Monica State Beach
Description: Santa Monica Beach is one of the most famous and attractive beaches in Los Angeles, with convenient transportation at the end of highway 10.

Name: Griffith Observatory
Description: Griffith Observatory is one of the world famous observatories. Located in the mountains northwest of the center of Los Angeles City, it is a great place to watch Hollywood signs and take a bird's-eye view of the whole city of Los Angeles.

Name: Palm Springs, California
Description: Palm Springs, located in the California desert, has long been a popular resort city. Palm Spring's hot desert climate makes it a winter resort in the United States, with sunny weather for more than 300 days a year.
